.TH "ata_build_rw_tf" 9 "ata_build_rw_tf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_build_rw_tf \- Build ATA taskfile for given read/write request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_build_rw_tf
.BI "(struct ata_taskfile *tf "  ","
.BI "struct ata_device *dev "  ","
.BI "u64 block "  ","
.BI "u32 n_block "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tf_flags "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tag "  ","
.BI "int class "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tf" 12
Target ATA taskfile
.IP "dev" 12
ATA device \fItf\fP belongs to
.IP "block" 12
Block address
.IP "n_block" 12
Number of blocks
.IP "tf_flags" 12
RW/FUA etc...
.IP "tag" 12
tag
.IP "class" 12
IO priority class

LOCKING:
None.

Build ATA taskfile \fItf\fP for read/write request described by
\fIblock\fP, \fIn_block\fP, \fItf_flags\fP and \fItag\fP on \fIdev\fP.
.SH "RETURN"

0 on success, -ERANGE if the request is too large for \fIdev\fP,
-EINVAL if the request is invalid.
